

--> The Linux truncate command is often used to shrink or extend the size of a file to the specified size..
--> if we truncate the file we would lost information and we never get it back.so be careful with truncate

   COMMAND SYNTAX:- truncate -s 10 filename   NOTE:- [shrinking of 30 bytes file to 10 bytes]
                    truncate -s 80 filename   NOTE:- [extending 30 bytes file to 80 bytes]
